# Event Management Platform – DevOps CI/CD Pipeline

## Overview

This project demonstrates the implementation of a complete DevOps ecosystem around a Spring Boot application for event management.

The platform integrates Continuous Integration, Continuous Delivery, code quality analysis, artifact management, containerization, automated deployment, and monitoring.

The objective is to automate the entire software delivery lifecycle from source code commit to deployment and observability.

---

## Features

* Event Management REST API
* Spring Boot Backend
* MySQL Database
* Automated Testing with JUnit & Mockito
* Code Coverage with JaCoCo
* Static Code Analysis with SonarQube
* Artifact Management with Nexus Repository
* Docker Containerization
* DockerHub Image Publishing
* Automated CI/CD Pipeline with Jenkins
* Monitoring with Prometheus
* Visualization with Grafana
* Container Monitoring with cAdvisor
* System Metrics with Node Exporter

---

## Architecture

![Architecture](screenshots/architecture.png)

### DevOps Ecosystem

| Component           | Technology     |
| ------------------- | -------------- |
| Source Control      | GitHub         |
| Backend             | Spring Boot    |
| Database            | MySQL          |
| CI/CD               | Jenkins        |
| Code Quality        | SonarQube      |
| Artifact Repository | Nexus 3        |
| Containerization    | Docker         |
| Image Registry      | DockerHub      |
| Deployment          | Docker Compose |
| Monitoring          | Prometheus     |
| Visualization       | Grafana        |
| Container Metrics   | cAdvisor       |
| Host Metrics        | Node Exporter  |

---

## CI/CD Pipeline

The Jenkins pipeline automatically executes on each push to GitHub.

### Continuous Integration

1. Source Code Checkout
2. Maven Build
3. Unit Testing
4. JaCoCo Coverage Analysis
5. SonarQube Analysis
6. Quality Gate Validation

### Continuous Delivery

1. Package Application
2. Publish Artifact to Nexus
3. Build Docker Image
4. Push Image to DockerHub
5. Deploy Complete Stack using Docker Compose

### Jenkins Pipeline

![Jenkins Pipeline](screenshots/jenkins.png)

